Diminishing Deterrence

	Philosophy

		-
			In general, the ability of a threat to deter individuals from pursuing a given course
			of action plateaus as the scale of the threat increases.
		-

	Principles

		Optimum Deterrent

			-
				The optimum deterrent is the point at which an increase in the scale of a threat no
				longer increases its ability to act as a deterrent. 
			-